## Hints & warnings
- The gate now lives at the TWO code-execution sites, not up-front: Op import (origin =
  _entity_of_project_id(source_project_id)) and load_op fallback (origin =
  ObjectRef.parse_uri(load_op_uri).entity, NOT the source project — this blocks the
  cross-entity redirect even from your own object). Data-only KNOWN types are never gated
  (they reconstruct in-process). Invariant: KNOWN_TYPES == SAFE_CUSTOM_WEAVE_TYPES ∪ {Op}.
- BEHAVIOR CHANGE: cross-entity code-bearing fetch now raises UnsafeDeserializationError
  by default. Opt back in with WEAVE_ALLOW_UNSAFE_CUSTOM_OBJ_DECODE=true.
- CAPABILITY NARROWING: previously WEAVE_ALLOW_UNSAFE_CUSTOM_OBJ_DECODE=false meant
  "refuse ALL code-bearing"; false is now the DEFAULT and means "entity-scoped"
  (same-entity allowed). The only fully-fail-closed path left is the worker
  (require_secure_weave_client). If someone needs a refuse-all-even-same-entity env knob,
  that's a follow-up (would need a separate setting).
- _assert_code_decode_allowed reads client._allow_unsafe_custom_obj_decode (the worker
  kill-switch, checked FIRST) and client.entity. Keep that ordering: worker fail-closed
  must win over the cross-entity opt-in.

